You are given a sequence of integers representing a binary tree in preorder traversal format, where -1 indicates a null node. Your task is to construct the binary tree from the given input and then print its preorder traversal.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer n, the number of elements in the array.

The second line contains n space-separated integers representing the preorder traversal of the binary tree.

The value -1 represents a null node.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

Print the preorder traversal of the constructed binary tree.

Output should be space-separated integers.

Sample Input 0

7
1 2 3 4 -1 -1 5
Sample Output 0

1 2 4 3 5
Sample Input 1

11
10 20 40 -1 -1 50 -1 -1 30 -1 -1
Sample Output 1

10 20 40 50 30
ANSWER:
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;
class Node
{
    int data;
    Node left,right;
    Node(int val)
    {
        data=val;
        left=right=null;
    }
}

public class Solution {
    static void preorder(Node root)
    {
        if(root==null) return;
        System.out.print(root.data+" ");
        preorder(root.left);
        preorder(root.right);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        /* Enter your code here. Read input from STDIN. Print output to STDOUT. Your class should be named Solution. */
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        int a[]=new int[n];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            a[i]=sc.nextInt();
        }
        Queue <Node> q=new LinkedList<>();
        Node root =new Node(a[0]);
        q.offer(root);
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++)
        {
            Node t=q.poll();
            if(a[i]!=-1)
            {
                Node l=new Node(a[i]);
                t.left=l;
                q.offer(l);
            }
            if(++i<n && a[i]!=-1)
            {
                Node r=new Node(a[i]);
                t.right=r;
                q.offer(r);
            }
        }
        preorder(root);
    }
}
